                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13961455" author="elyograg" created="Sun, 6 Apr 2014 16:35:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What exactly do you mean by &quot;unable to view the full list&quot; in your description?  I look at the screenshot you provided and I don&apos;t see a problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13961459" author="erickerickson" created="Sun, 6 Apr 2014 16:51:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve seen this before, especially on IE but also on other browsers. On the left side you can&apos;t click on &quot;schema browser&quot; which is below &quot;replication&quot;, and this latter partially cut off. And you can&apos;t scroll that part of the screen so especially with some combinations of remote viewing, Webex, projecting your desktop on a shared screen (and the screen resolution is changed) and the like, some parts of the screen become inaccessible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13961468" author="elyograg" created="Sun, 6 Apr 2014 17:36:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now that Erick has cleared up what I couldn&apos;t figure out, I do see the problem.  It&apos;s also a problem on 4.6.1 and 4.2.1, the other versions that I have available for quick trial.  I never noticed this because I&apos;ve always got a high resolution display and my browser takes up most of the screen area.  This is a problem for people who are using ultra-light laptops that rarely have much in the way of vertical resolution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One workaround is the zoom feature in the browser, which can usually be accessed by holding down the ctrl key and turning the zoom wheel on the mouse.  Ctrl-0 (zero) will reset to normal on both IE and Firefox.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13961470" author="elyograg" created="Sun, 6 Apr 2014 17:44:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you do happen to be on a laptop with a touchpad, most modern touchpads can emulate the scroll wheel with the right edge of the touchpad.  Or you can access the browser&apos;s menu and change the zoom level there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m aware that as workarounds go, this is not a very good one, but it should work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13961480" author="amantandon3091" created="Sun, 6 Apr 2014 18:18:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks sir, actually the tested browser is chrome and its version is 33.0.1750.154&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13975224" author="steffkes" created="Sun, 20 Apr 2014 18:58:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve updated the issue title, it&apos;s not a windows-specific problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;attached a first version of the patch, which uses an additional class to switch between different &apos;modes&apos;. one (still) fixed, if the viewport is big enough, the other scrollable, in case you can&apos;t see the menu all at once. it&apos;s checked when the page loads, the menu changes and when you resize your browser window.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13982142" author="aman tandon" created="Sat, 26 Apr 2014 23:56:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, this will be great &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With Regards&lt;br/&gt;
Aman Tandon&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;On Mon, Apr 21, 2014 at 12:29 AM, Stefan Matheis (steffkes) (JIRA) &amp;lt;&lt;/p&gt;
